                       "message":  "PROJECT-SAVE-SUBSTRATE: add save_project_world_to_path (.rge-project writer)\n\nNo .rge-project writer existed — save_scene_world_to_path rejected it with a\n\"deferred to a follow-up\" note. This adds the lib substrate: write a live World\nback to an existing .rge-project by overwriting its first scene and re-writing\nthe manifest. The save-side inverse of the .rge-project branch of\nload_scene_world_from_path, mirroring its resolution exactly (exact .rge-project\nname; scenes.first(); project-parent-relative path) so a save -\u003e load\nround-trips.\n\n- save_project_world_to_path(world, project_path): exact-name gate -\u003e read +\n  RON-parse the manifest -\u003e resolve the first scene relative to the project\n  parent -\u003e reuse save_scene_world_to_path for the scene write -\u003e re-stamp\n  SchemaVersion::V0_1_0 + re-serialize the manifest.\n- ProjectWorldSaveError: distinct failure modes (UnsupportedExtension / Read /\n  ParseProject / EmptyProjectScenes / ProjectHasNoParentDir / Scene /\n  SerializeManifest / WriteManifest).\n- Retired the stale \"deferred to a follow-up\" prose on save_scene_world_to_path\n  + its UnsupportedExtension variant.\n\nPart 1 of in-app .rge-project save (the serialization-bearing substrate); the\neditor source-model + routing + binary hook are part 2 (mirrors\nSCENE-SAVE-SUBSTRATE -\u003e WIRING). No editor / binary / Cargo.toml change, no\nunsafe. Tests: 5 round-trip + error-path tests (save -\u003e load preserves the\nworld; manifest preserved; rejection paths). Canonical gate green.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
