                       "message":  "PROJECT-SAVE-SUBSTRATE: refresh stale follow-up comment in scene test (post-exec doc fix)\n\nPost-exec correction (comment-only; no behavior change). The PR landed\nsave_project_world_to_path, so the comment in scene_save_round_trip.rs saying\nthe literal .rge-project is rejected because \"project write + manifest update is\na follow-up\" is now false. Updated it to note the SCENE writer rejects\n.rge-project and that projects are written via save_project_world_to_path; the\ntest behavior (save_scene_world_to_path still rejects .rge-project) is unchanged.\n\nRepo-wide sweep confirms this was the only stale reference — lib.rs:606\u0027s\n\"creating a NEW project tree (Save-As) is a follow-up\" remains accurate (that\ncase is genuinely still deferred).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
